-- South Korea Department Store Sales Rise 2.9% in February
-- B y   R o s e   K i m
-- 2012-03-18T21:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-18/south-korea-department-store-sales-rise-2-9-in-february.html
Sales at major South Korean
department stores rose last month as cold weather boosted demand
for clothing.  Outlays (KODSDEPT)  at the three largest chains rose 2.9 percent in
February from a year earlier, following a 4.1 percent decline in
January, the Ministry of  Knowledge Economy  said in a statement
today. Discount-store sales dropped 6.4 percent, todayâ€™s report
